.TH abort-command 2
.XI abort-command - "\*(C0Abort command"
.SH NAME
abort-command \- Abort command
.Me $a
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBabort-command\fR \*(C0
.SH DESCRIPTION
Aborts the current  command, when in trouble, this command will usually  limit
the  damage. If you find  yourself  in a position  where you do not want to be
then this  command  will  usually  take you back to a sane state. This command
rings the bell and stops keyboard macros.
.PP
Avoid re-binding this key where possible as it is used in other places.
.PP
When
.B abort-command
is  invoked  a warning is automatically given alerting  the user, this may be
an audible or a visual warning depending on the global state of the
.Ht quiet 5
global variable.
